  <prompt>
    Create a Power Apps view named "Playbook Index Drift" on the `sprk_analysisplaybook` entity that filters `sprk_indexstatus IN ('stale', 'failed', 'not-indexed')`. Columns: name, `sprk_playbookcode`, `sprk_indexstatus`, `sprk_lastindexedat`, `sprk_lastindexerror`. Ribbon includes "Send to Index" (from task 033). Implements spec FR-14.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE Power Apps engineer. Expert in saved-query authoring + FetchXml + model-driven app view configuration.</role>

  <goal>
    "Playbook Index Drift" view appears under `sprk_analysisplaybook` in the admin model-driven app. Filter matches the 3 status values. Ribbon includes the "Send to Index" button per task 033. Visible to admin role only.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-14 + design §1.4. Single Dataverse `savedquery` row authored via Web API or solution editor. Admins use this view to find playbooks needing reindex; ribbon enables bulk "Send to Index" trigger.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/dataverse/solutions/</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/design.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-14: view name exactly "Playbook Index Drift"; filter is `sprk_indexstatus IN ('stale', 'failed', 'not-indexed')`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">View must be solution-aware (added to the unmanaged solution so it deploys with task 039).</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
